---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import CTABlock from '../../components/CTABlock.astro';
import BlogHero from '../../components/BlogHero.astro';
import BlogFigure from '../../components/BlogFigure.astro';
import RelatedPosts from '../../components/RelatedPosts.astro';
import { business, BASE } from '../../data/business';
import { postBySlug, postsBySlugs, RELATED_POSTS } from '../../data/posts';

const post = postBySlug('sleeper-raised-bed-landscaping-ayrshire')!;
const relatedPosts = postsBySlugs(RELATED_POSTS[post.slug] ?? []).slice(0, 3);
const siteUrl = business.siteUrl.replace(/\/$/, '');
const url = `${siteUrl}/blog/${post.slug}/`;
const ogImage = `${siteUrl}${BASE}/gallery/ayrshire-raised-sleeper-bed-landscaping-19-1600w.jpg`;

const articleSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  '@id': `${url}#article`,
  headline: post.title,
  description: post.description,
  inLanguage: 'en-GB',
  datePublished: post.date,
  dateModified: post.date,
  author: { '@type': 'Person', name: post.author, worksFor: { '@id': `${siteUrl}/#business` } },
  publisher: { '@id': `${siteUrl}/#business` },
  image: [ogImage],
  mainEntityOfPage: url,
  keywords: [post.keyword],
  wordCount: post.wordCount,
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`${post.title} | Sorn Handyman Services`}
  description={post.description}
  canonicalPath={`/blog/${post.slug}/`}
  ogImage={ogImage}
  ogType="article"
  extraSchema={articleSchema}
>
  <Breadcrumbs trail={[
    { name: 'Home', href: `${BASE}/` },
    { name: 'Blog', href: `${BASE}/blog/` },
    { name: post.title },
  ]} />

  <article class="container-x py-10 lg:py-14 max-w-3xl">
    <header>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-amber-600">
        <span>{post.area}</span>
        <span aria-hidden class="text-navy-900/20">·</span>
        <span class="text-navy-900/60">{post.readMinutes} min read</span>
        <span aria-hidden class="text-navy-900/20">·</span>
        <time datetime={post.date} class="text-navy-900/60">{post.dateDisplay}</time>
      </div>
      <h1 class="mt-4 font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-navy-900 leading-tight">
        {post.title}
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg text-navy-900/75">
        A garden refurb in Ayrshire — a new sleeper raised bed built into the
        corner, fresh topsoil in, and a young Rowan tree planted at the heart
        of it. Supply and install throughout.
      </p>
    </header>

    <BlogHero slug="ayrshire-raised-sleeper-bed-landscaping-19" />

    <div class="prose-sorn mt-8 text-lg cv-auto">
      <h2>What the job involved</h2>
      <p>
        The bed was set out on the ground first so the customer could see
        the shape before a single sleeper was cut. Once the footprint was
        right, sleepers were cut to length, drilled and pinned together with
        long timber screws, courses staggered so every joint had full timber
        behind it.
      </p>
      <p>
        The bed was back-filled with a layer of drainage and then fresh
        topsoil, the Rowan was planted centrally with room for its roots to
        spread, and the surrounding ground was dressed off. A tidy corner
        that will fill out over the next couple of seasons.
      </p>

      <BlogFigure slug="ayrshire-raised-sleeper-bed-landscaping-19" />

      <h2>Things to think about before you start</h2>
      <p>
        Sleepers are heavy and long. Check access from the van to the garden
        before you commit to a bed in the far corner — narrow gates, tight
        steps and soft lawns all change the day on site. If the sleepers
        have to go over a fence, factor that in.
      </p>
      <p>
        Pick the tree with the spot in mind, not the other way round. A Rowan
        stays neat and handles Ayrshire weather well, which is why it turns
        up so often in small gardens. Bigger species can outgrow a raised
        bed inside a few years, and the roots end up the problem you were
        trying to avoid.
      </p>

      <p>
        If you are in Ayrshire and need something similar, Fraser will come
        and look for free. Call <strong>07900 255876</strong> or WhatsApp
        <strong>+44 7472 223323</strong>. FREE no-obligation quote, every job
        priced individually.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 rounded-2xl border border-navy-900/10 bg-navy-50/50 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm text-navy-900/60">Written by</p>
        <p class="mt-1 font-serif text-xl font-bold text-navy-900">{post.author}</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-navy-900/75 text-sm">{post.authorBio}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  {relatedPosts.length > 0 && (
    <RelatedPosts posts={relatedPosts} eyebrow="Keep reading" heading="Related posts" variant="tinted" />
  )}

  <CTABlock
    heading="Corner of the garden begging for a lift?"
    sub="A raised bed and the right planting can transform a plot. Fraser will come and walk it."
    location="Ayrshire"
  />
</BaseLayout>
